
GIT HOOKS & GPG SIGNING SETUP
==============================

A lightweight guide to set up local Git hooks and GPG-signed commits
for secure and consistent workflows.

This configuration ensures every commit follows the correct message
format and is cryptographically signed.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Make Git Hooks Executable
------------------------------------------------------------------------

Enable executable permissions for your local Git hooks:

    > chmod +x .githooks/commit-msg
    # Optional:
    # chmod +x .githooks/pre-commit
    # chmod +x .githooks/pre-push

Tell Git to use your local .githooks directory:

    > git config core.hooksPath .githooks
